The snippet of your bean configuration looks correct; however note that 
a MatchesListRegexDecideRule may (like many other rules) be configured 
to either ACCEPT the URIs that match, or REJECT the URIs that match.

The default (inherited from PredicatedDecideRule) is to ACCEPT. So if 
you want your rule to REJECT, you need to add...

  &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;REJECT&quot;/&gt;

...to your rule, to override the default.

We should probably add the default &quot;ACCEPT&quot; to the commented-out example 
settings on our bundled configurations, as with other defaults, to 
remind people that this is changeable and default-ACCEPT.

Hope this helps,

- Gordon @ IA

